## 2026-04-03 - HistoryPanel has no redo
- Implemented server-side redo stack for rolled-back operations:
  - `operation-log.ts`: `rollback()` now returns `{ restoredPaths, rollbackEntryId }` — the ID of the newly created rollback entry, enabling the client to track which operation can re-rollback it as a redo
  - `useRecentOperations.ts`: Added `redoEntries` state (array of `{ origOpId, rollbackId, description }`). `handleRollback` now pushes to redo entries on success. New `handleServerRedo(opId?)` function that calls rollback on the stored rollback entry ID, then pops it from the redo stack. Exposes `canServerRedo`, `serverRedoDescription`, `redoableOpIds` (Set of original op IDs with redo available)

